04/06/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Construction of a railroad project under Corridor 8 has started in Albania, according to local media reports Thursday (3 June). 
Italian Army specialists have started two stretches: rebuilding the line from the port city of Durres to Shkozet in western Albania, and building a new line from Lin village in southeast Albania to the border with Macedonia. 
The start of construction is viewed as a major achievement by Albanian authorities, as the project is considered essential for the country. 
Officials from Albania and Italy attended the groundbreaking ceremony. 
(Albanian Daily News - 04/06/04)
